author: @muhammadabdullahdilshad8509
text: A sample Small Students Database Project  student_record = []  """The Function adds a Student Record""" def add_student_record(name, age, course):     student_record.append({'name': name, 'age': age, 'course': course})   """The function Displays all the availabel Students""" def view_students():     for record in student_record:         print(record['name'])   """The Function Searches for a particular student in the list of students""" def search_student(name, age, course):     for record in student_record:         if record['name'] == name and record['age'] == age and record['course'] == course:             return record     return None   """The Function Updates the Student Record in the List of available Students""" def update_student(name,age,course,new_name,new_age,new_course):     for record in student_record:         if record['name'] == name and record['age'] == age and record['course'] == course:             record.update({'name':new_name,'age':new_age,'course':new_course})             return     return 0  while True:     print("1. Add a Student")     print("2. View Students")     print("3. Search a Student")     print("4. Update a Student")     print("6. Exit")      choice = int(input("What is your choice: "))      if choice == 1:         name = input("Name of a Student: ")         age = int(input("Age of a Student: "))         course = input("Student Course: ")         add_student_record(name, age, course)         print("Student Record has been Successfully added")      elif choice == 2:         print("All the Students are:")         view_students()      elif choice == 3:         name = input("Enter the name of the student you want to search: ")         age = int(input("Enter the age of the student: "))         course = input("Enter the course of the student: ")         searched_student = search_student(name, age, course)         if searched_student:             print(f"{searched_student['name']} Age: {searched_student['age']} with course {searched_student['course']} has been Found")         else:             print("Student Not Found")     elif choice == 4:         name = input("Enter the name of the student you want to Update: ")         age = int(input("Enter the age of the student: "))         course = input("Enter the course of the student: ")          new_name = input("Enter the new name of the student : ")         new_age = int(input("Enter the new age of the student: "))         new_course = input("Enter the new course of the student: ")          output = update_student(name,age,course,new_name,new_age,new_course)         if output == 0:           print("Student Not Found")         else:             print("Student Record has been updated succesfully")      elif choice == 6:         print("Exiting the System")         break      else:         print("Invalid Choice. Please Try Again.")

author: @brainplot
text: Hi Corey! This is a really great tutorial! Thank you! Can I just suggest you a handy Sublime shortcut? :D Since I saw you copied and pasted lines when you needed to duplicate them in multiple rows, I would like to tell you that you can hit cmd+shift+d while the cursor is at any point of the line and it'll get duplicated. It's even faster than just copy and paste! Once you've got the hang of it, you'll feel its lack in any other text editor :)
